abstract: Her Crime column leads with Jeff Lindsay’s worthy successor to Dexter, his enticingly twisted serial killer — Riley Wolfe, a devilish master thief.
snippet: Her Crime column leads with Jeff Lindsay’s worthy successor to Dexter, his enticingly twisted serial killer — Riley Wolfe, a devilish master thief.
lead_paragraph: Poor Riley Wolfe, the devilishly charming antihero of Jeff Lindsay’s witty caper mystery JUST WATCH ME (Dutton, $26), the first volume in a new series — now that Dexter, the twisted serial killer at the center of Lindsay’s previous books, has gone to his reward. Riley, a master thief, has just pulled off the extraordinary feat of stealing a 12½-ton, $50 million steel statue and ridding the world of the loathsome head of a pharmaceutical empire who donated this monstrosity to the city of Chicago. So, why so glum, chum? “It had all been too easy,” he explains, “and I hate that.”

abstract: This week, Lauretta Charlton reviews Darryl Pinckney’s collection of essays “Busted in New York.” In 1992, Edmund White wrote for the Book Review about “High Cotton,” Pinckney’s debut novel about a young black man coming of age.

abstract: British lawmakers gave preliminary approval Friday to Prime Minister Boris Johnson’s Brexit bill, clearing the way for the U.K. to leave the European Union next month.
snippet: British lawmakers gave preliminary approval Friday to Prime Minister Boris Johnson’s Brexit bill, clearing the way for the U.K. to leave the European Union next month.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — British lawmakers gave preliminary approval Friday to Prime Minister Boris Johnson’s Brexit bill, clearing the way for the U.K. to leave the European Union next month.
headline_main: UK Lawmakers OK Johnson's Brexit Bill, Pave Way to Exit EU
headline_print_headline: UK Lawmakers OK Johnson's Brexit Bill, Pave Way to Exit EU

abstract: A Libyan force fighting to capture the country's capital from the U.N.-supported government based there on Friday gave the militias defending Tripoli a three-day deadline to pull out.
snippet: A Libyan force fighting to capture the country's capital from the U.N.-supported government based there on Friday gave the militias defending Tripoli a three-day deadline to pull out.
lead_paragraph: CAIRO — A Libyan force fighting to capture the country's capital from the U.N.-supported government based there on Friday gave the militias defending Tripoli a three-day deadline to pull out.
headline_main: Libyan Force Attacking Tripoli Gives Militias 3-Day Deadline
headline_print_headline: Libyan Force Attacking Tripoli Gives Militias 3-Day Deadline
